    "description": "Through our dedicated associates, Conduent delivers mission-critical services and solutions on behalf of Fortune 100 companies and over 500 governments \u2013 creating exceptional outcomes for our clients and the millions of people who count on them.\n\nYou have an opportunity to personally thrive, make a difference and be part of a culture where individuality is noticed and valued every day\n\nJob Description\n\nThe Governance, Risk and Compliance (GRC) Data Analyst II reports to the Senior Director, Cybersecurity & Technology Risk and will work with a team of five full-time risk and governance professionals and cross-functionally across Global Risk. Primary accountabilities include cataloging, reviewing, analyzing, and providing governance, risk, and compliance driven metrics and insights using multiple data sources and analytic tools. These tools primarily consist of SharePoint and PowerBI but may include other data sources and analytic capabilities. This individual should have familiarity with information technology controls, key performance indicators, and key risk indicators.\n\nThe GRC Data Analyst II will help develop and implement an overall cybersecurity and technology metrics strategy, transform data into insight and insight into key performance and risk indicators that will help inform and drive cyber & tech risk decisions. This individual will help ensure that data and metrics are relevant and that the processes used to collect, analyze and visualize, and sustainable at an enterprise level.\n\nThis individual may be based remotely and should be open to occasional travel as necessary.\n\nAccountabilities\n\u2022 Gather, manage, and analyze information from specified data sources. This data source will primarily be SharePoint but may include other data sources as required\n\u2022 In conjunction with other team members, help drive the development of Key Performance Indicators (KPI) and Key Risk Indicators (KRI)\n\u2022 Assist in creating and presenting KPIs and KRIs\n\u2022 Develop, publish, and maintain process documents to enable and ensure successful recurring data collection, analysis, and reporting\n\u2022 Use analytic tools (Power BI) to develop graphs, infographics and other methods to visualize data\n\u2022 Utilizing SharePoint as the primary GRC platform, work with a global team in various GRC platform administration responsibilities, including evaluation, design, and implementation of new capabilities. Execute administrative tasks in the GRC platform to support ongoing use such as data collection, report generation, record status monitoring and tracking, user and workflow management\n\u2022 Work as a point of contact and subject matter expert for GRC platform information requests and issue management and escalations\n\u2022 Facilitate requirements design, development, testing, implementations, and on-going support and administration of the SharePoint GRC platform\n\nRequired Qualifications\n\u2022 Minimum Bachelor\u2019s Degreein Computer Science, Information Technology, Data Analytics, or related field\n\u2022 Experience with designing and developing PowerBI dashboards\n\u2022 Experience in utilizing or developing SharePoint-based platforms\n\nDesired Qualifications\n\u2022 Understanding of technology and cybersecurity concepts and principles\n\u2022 Industry knowledge in enterprise-level information technology architecture, operations, and cybersecurity operations\n\u2022 Holds certifications in one or more areas related to cyber or information security (e.g., Security+, CISSP, CISA, etc.).\n\nQualities/Attributes\n\u2022 Impeccable integrity\n\u2022 Exceptional professional presence\n\u2022 Polished, effective, and credible communicator\n\u2022 Highly organized with a delivery focus\n\u2022 Strategic thinker\n\u2022 Possesses and demonstrates sound judgment\n\u2022 Accountable\n\u2022 Relationship builder with a partnering philosophy and mindset\n\u2022 Transparent, collaborative operating style\n\u2022 Leads by example, fostering an appropriate high-performance team culture of accountability\n\nClosing\n\nConduent is an Equal Opportunity Employer and considers applicants for all positions without regard to race, color, creed, religion, ancestry, national origin, age, gender identity, gender expression, sex/gender, marital status, sexual orientation, physical or mental disability, medical condition, use of a guide dog or service animal, military/veteran status, citizenship status, basis of genetic information, or any other group protected by law.\n\nPeople with disabilities who need a reasonable accommodation to apply for or compete for employment with Conduent may request such accommodation(s) by clicking on the following link, completing the accommodation request form, and submitting the request by using the \u201cSubmit\u201d button at the bottom of the form. For those using Google Chrome or Mozilla Firefox please download the form first: click here to access or download the form. You may also click here to access Conduent\u2019s ADAAA Accommodation Policy.\n\nAt Conduent we value the health and safety of our associates, their families and our community. For US applicants while we DO NOT require vaccination for most of our jobs, we DO require that you provide us with your vaccination status, where legally permissible. Providing this information is a requirement of your employment at Conduent"
